    {
      "kind": "parameters",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A  rendering context.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "ctx"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A virtual screen number, which must be a value between ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "0",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " and the number of virtual screens minus one. You can obtain the number of virtual screens available associated with a rendering context by calling the function ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.agl/documentation/AGL/AGL-collection",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ", passing in the pixel format object used to create the rendering context and the attribute constant ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "AGL_VIRTUAL_SCREEN",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": ".",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "screen"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return-value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Returns ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GL_FALSE",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " if it fails for any reason, ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GL_TRUE",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " otherwise. If an error occurs, call the function ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.agl/documentation/AGL/aglGetError",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to determine what the error is.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You should use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "aglSetVirtualScreen",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " function only when it is necessary to override the default behavior. The current virtual screen is normally set automatically by the functions ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.agl/documentation/AGL/aglSetDrawable",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.agl/documentation/AGL/aglUpdateContext",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". Setting the virtual screen forces the renderer associated with the virtual screen to process OpenGL commands issued to the specified context. Changing the virtual screen changes the current renderer. Because the current virtual screen determines which OpenGL renderer is processing commands, the return values of all ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "glGetXXX",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " functions can be affected by the current virtual screen.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For detailed information on virtual screens, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/GraphicsImaging/Conceptual/OpenGL-MacProgGuide/opengl_intro/opengl_intro.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40001987",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
